author: COMSOL
description:
Carefully controlled injection mold cooling is very important to attain a desired cooling history of plastic molds, since the structural integrity of the material depends on the cooling history.

This example demonstrates how the Pipe Flow Module can be used to model the cooling of an injection-molded polyurethane part for a car steering wheel.
